```json
{
"application": "Slurm",
"details": {
"job_name": "Elva paper winter experiments videos",
"time": "20:00:00",
"cpus_per_task": 1,
"partition": "main",
"array": "0-33",
"modules": "any/python/3.8.3-conda",
"conda_env": "ros2",
"working_directory": "/gpfs/space/home/rometaid/nvidia-e2e/viz",
"script": "./create_driving_video.sh",
"script_arguments": "${DATASETS[$SLURM_ARRAY_TASK_ID]}"
}
}
```

The script uses the Slurm Workload Manager to manage the execution of the `create_driving_video.sh` script.

The script runs in an array of 34 jobs (0-33), each processing a different dataset from the `DATASETS` array.

The script requires a specific Python version (3.8.3) and a conda environment named "ros2" to be loaded. 

It also runs the `create_driving_video.sh` script in a specific directory, `/gpfs/space/home/rometaid/nvidia-e2e/viz`. 

The `create_driving_video.sh` script takes a single argument, which is the dataset name to process.
